# Codex Tasks — Aim Brain Engine

## Task 1 — Engine Skeleton

Create `src/engine/` with module folders for types, stats, ranks, scenarios, diagnosis, recommendations, coach, and index.

Deliverables:

- `analyzeAimProfile()` exported from `src/engine/index.ts`
- initial TypeScript types
- sample data fixture
- one basic test or debug script

## Task 2 — Score Stats

Implement:

- latest score
- personal best
- all-run average
- last-5 average
- last-10 average
- total runs
- run count by scenario
- accepted-only filtering

## Task 3 — Consistency and Confidence

Implement first version:

- consistency from recent run variance
- confidence from last-10 average vs PB, consistency, and sample size
- readable confidence labels

## Task 4 — Scenario Matching

Implement:

- scenario name normalization
- exact canonical match
- alias match
- platform-aware matching
- unresolved match output

Do not auto-confirm fuzzy matches silently.

## Task 5 — Rank Progress

Implement:

- threshold lookup by scenario and benchmark set
- rank band detection
- progress to next rank
- progress-only fallback when threshold data is missing

Never invent rank data.

## Task 6 — Category Analysis

Implement:

- category grouping
- category average strength
- category confidence
- category volume
- strongest and weakest category
- most neglected category

## Task 7 — Weakness Detector

Implement a transparent weak-link score using:

- target gap
- consistency penalty
- recency penalty
- volume deficit
- decay/freshness risk placeholder

Return both score and explanation.

## Task 8 — Training Recommender

Implement:

- session type
- priority categories
- avoid-overtraining categories
- recommended scenarios
- reason for each recommendation
- success condition

## Task 9 — Coach Summary

Implement rule-based summary templates.

The coach summary must include:

- what is strong
- what is blocking progress
- what to train today
- why that recommendation was made

## Task 10 — UI Connection

Update Home/Summary/Coach screens to display engine output.

Do not duplicate engine calculations in UI components.
